beer.beer_description:
A delicate session ale, lightly hopped with subtle stone fruit characters to complement crisp, pale golden malt flavours. Designed to be joyfully consumed during the uplifting season of spring, without too much overthinking.

Look: Bright pale gold
Aroma: Subtle stone fruit
Taste: Subtle apricot, peach, delicate crisp malt, balanced bitterness

beer.beer_description: Our troublesome original release, named for the problematic first brew day which hugely emphasised its hop bitterness. It's matured and evolved nicely over the years, with us. Big tropical hop flavour from local varieties with strong bitterness from an English hop to honour its origins, all balanced by plenty of malt.

Our feathered friends see the world differently. Through birds’ eyes, things might look almost psychedelic to us, with heightened colours and fresh hues forming a surprising new spectrum. This hazy, citrus and stonefruit accented IPA with a mellow, soft and silky texture gives a similarly refreshing change of perspective.

beer.beer_description:
A good watchdog is the perfect companion, a relaxed and friendly presence but always alert and attentive. It’s a rare mix of traits but our brewers have taught a similar trick to this Watchdog, a refreshingly non-alcoholic IPA, with a pale malt backbone and lively hop flavours of citrus and stonefruit, but no bite.

< 0.5% alc./vol.

beer.beer_description:
When the cliché was coined that dogs are humanity's best friends, it was a Greyhound they had in mind. Whether your plans involve a run or a rest, a greyhound is up for joining in. We've dedicated our low carb hazy pale ale to them, and kept it fittingly lean and easy-going, with sparkling citrus hop characters, good balance, and
a crisp finish.

Contains 50% less carbs than other Parrotdog beers.

Bright and lively like a parrot, but small and ubiquitous like a sparrow, the Yellowhammer adds a flash of colour and a musical chirp to open spaces all over the country. The way it does a lot with just a little inspires our smooth and refreshing hazy pale ale, streaked with the striking tropical notes of Strata hops.

Kiwis, rugby and sheep aren’t the only things New Zealand has to offer. There’s a ton of great beers in a variety of styles just waiting for you to explore! That’s 5 beers from a brewery in New Zealand. Try 5 more for Level 2.

beer.beer_description: Our troublesome original release, named for the problematic first brew day which hugely emphasised its hop bitterness. It's matured and evolved nicely over the years, with us. Big tropical hop flavour from local varieties with strong bitterness from an English hop to honour its origins, all balanced by plenty of malt.

Our feathered friends see the world differently. Through birds’ eyes, things might look almost psychedelic to us, with heightened colours and fresh hues forming a surprising new spectrum. This hazy, citrus and stonefruit accented IPA with a mellow, soft and silky texture gives a similarly refreshing change of perspective.

Falcons stalk the skies, commanding their territory with focus and intensity; a totem for this American Pale Ale. 

Our interpretation of the style takes modern U.S. hop flavours of citrus and tropical fruit and lets them soar on a light and nimble body.

Hazy IPA brewed with American Hops.
Malts: NZ Ale, Oats, Wheat, Light Caramel
Hops: Citra, Mosaic, Amarillo
Yeast: East Coast Ale

Hazy IPA brewed with Australian Hops. 
Malts: Maris Otter, Oats, Wheat,Light Crystal 
Hops: Galaxy, Vic Secret, Enigma
Yeast: East Coast Ale
Malthouse West Coast IPA Challenge 2018 Champion.

Bright and lively like a parrot, but small and ubiquitous like a sparrow, the Yellowhammer adds a flash of colour and a musical chirp to open spaces all over the country. The way it does a lot with just a little inspires our smooth and refreshing hazy pale ale, streaked with the striking tropical notes of Strata hops.

His standards were strict, and his decision determined what was in or out; he was gatekeeper to the masses. But we’d like to think we would’ve won Terry over with this, a complex mix of dark malts with lashings of coconut threads and cacao nibs. Fitting tribute to a good man who loved a good stout.

Rhys had a knack for mixing things together in delightful ways. He always made sure the bar was a beautiful blend of drinks and drinkers from all over, and it was his inspired idea to combine coconut with the juicy tropical fruit flavours of a modern hazy IPA — pineapple colliding with sharp citrus and smooth coconut, for a perfect escape.

Refreshingly uncomplicated.

A Classic lager brewed with New Zealand’s distinctive and underappreciated Green Bullet hop.

Lloyd looked upon the mechanised marvel of the modern canning line where his son worked and could only summon one word: Wow. He’d be equally enthused with this, too: a Hazy IPA packed with fresh tropical fruit and citrus flavour thanks to the help of a promising new NZ hop variety.

On the long trip from Washington to Wellington, Lindsay wondered how easily she’d make new friends. And now it’s all gone so well that she’s decided to stay. This West Coast IPA — a one-off that proved such a crowd-pleaser that it’s decided to return, too — has a winning combination of stone fruit and citrus flavours thanks to a relatively new and underrated U.S. hop, Cashmere, all the way from Lindsay’s home state.

New Zealand grows more boysenberries than anywhere else, thanks to people like Glen. The fruit from his farm gives this beer its maroon hue and tart berry flavour, complementing the clean, refreshing acidity that comes from its kettle-souring at our brewery, with the help of a few million Lactobacillus bacteria.

Adrian’s sense of style was all about taking a classic and revving it up a little, like the race-
ready version of an otherwise familiar car: its engine a bit bigger, its lines and livery a bit
bolder. This hazy IPA, powered by the freshly
prototyped new hop Strata and roaring with its
dank tropical fruit notes, would suit him nicely.

Our original release takes on a fresh new look this autumn, using unprocessed Freestyle Hops hop cones picked from the bine and flown across the Cook Strait to make their way into the brewhouse all on the same day. Two different hop varieties lend their distinctive white grape and freshly squeezed lime characters to create one harmonious batch of Fresh Hop Bitterbitch.

beer.beer_style: IPA - Imperial / Double New England / Hazy
beer.beer_description: Peter’s imposing stature disguised his true nature, and it was usually when you first heard his laugh rumbling across the room, that you realised he was the gentlest of giants. This Double Hazy IPA has a similarly huge presence, but its ripples of juiciness from three different citrus-heavy hop varieties ring out through the haze, and keep it just as unexpectedly approachable as he was.

Tina tended her garden with the care of a master horticulturist, patiently propagating new varieties of her favourite plants, always searching for that revolutionary hybrid. The ripe fruit flavours of this hazy IPA — citrus, tropical, even a little stonefruit — come from Nectaron, a newly-released cultivar and the result of years of similar work in the hop fields of New Zealand. A fine tribute to Tina and all her botanical friends.

If the sky is clear and cool, and you’re very lucky, you might witness a sundog: apparitions that accompany the true sun, an atmospheric trick of light and ice. Our own Sundog, a pilsner starring the vivid passionfruit and white wine notes of New Zealand hops, is much easier to find, but just as crisp and bright.

Robert, or ‘Bob’ as his mother calls him, had always been stronger than he looked, but known to be a sweet and gentle soul. Coffee Supreme has poured itself into creating this unique white coffee stout with us. Brewed using no dark malts at all, Robert sees Maris Otter, wheat, Munich and Vienna malts combine with rolled oats to form a deceivingly stout, yet pale, foundation. Coffee Supreme Brazil Bob-O-Link coffee beans, along with cacao nibs, are added to the beer following fermentation to lend smooth ‘stout-like’ characters – without any of the typical dark colour.

You always knew when Janice was in the room – really big vibes. Her humongous presence filled the space as much as her buoyant personality lifted the mood. We hope we’ve captured that spirit with this bold and lively IIPA that’s positively bursting with zesty and lush hop character. Long live Janice.

Brent wasn’t the type to let a difficult year spoil the work of decades. The family farm had persevered through all kinds of bad weather, both literal and metaphorical, but his friends always got what they needed from his fields. This hazy IPA is heaped full of freshly-harvested Nectaron®, the brash new hop variety that adds a dash of stone fruit flavour to the classic combination of citrus and tropical fruit. It’s the pick of the crop, to welcome a fresh start.

From the bine to the brewery as fast as possible, four hundred kilos of the freshest Nelson Sauvin hops give their distinctive “white wine” character to this juicy pale ale made in the modern New England style.

Bruce remembers the harvest before the hop machine. Tales of a bygone era, when the village would come together alongside his trusty Clydesdales, working hand and hoof to bring in the season’s crop. This year we celebrate a present day coming-together in our Fresh Hop Hazy IPA. Two hop varieties, Nectaron® and Riwaka, combine to create tropical waves of nectarine and grapefruit. A friendly blend we’d hope to find Bruce pouring for the people come beer o’clock.

Steve never tired of his work. He’d been there as long as anyone could remember, mentoring his colleagues and marshaling their collective effort to loftier heights than they felt capable of individually. He would’ve admired the hours of effort from the teams in the fields, the lab, and the brewery that all went into this beer — and the result, a hazy IPA bursting with tropical, stone fruit and citrus characters thanks to the clever new Cryo Pop™ blend which is refreshing in more ways than one.

This Matt is a Hazy IPA, a style we’ve seen really take off during our time, its soft juiciness causing a lot of fun and winning a lot of fans, including us. Recently released hop varieties Nectaron® and Ekuanot, as well as Citra, give this one lush waves of mango, mandarin, passionfruit and pineapple.
